This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object detection. The use of boosted decision trees also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper proposes an efficient feature transform, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of decision trees also suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper proposes a method to reduce false positives, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
